I have also had trouble building if I select a fold that is write protected somehow. We have in the past stored our code in a dropbox and google drive. If you launch your code from those folders, it will try to by default build into that folder. For some reason, some of those files become write protected and the build will fail.

To change you go to the project, right click on Build Specifications >> right click on FRC Robot Boot-up Deployment>> Properties>> Destination and then change the Destination Path.

It took me 3 days to figure out this years ago when I first started using LabVIEW.
